            . I am shopman to Mrs. Ann Harlow, a widow, who lives in <placeName id="t18260622-87-crimeloc422">Norton Falgate</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18260622-87-crimeloc422" type="placeName" value="Norton Falgate"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18260622-87-crimeloc422" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260622-87-off419 t18260622-87-crimeloc422"></join>. I saw the prisoner come there on the 5th of June, about seven o'clock in the evening - he asked the price of a tortoiseshell snuff-box - I said 25s., and was going to take it out of the window; he said he thought it had not been above 4s. or 5s.; I then said I had some at 3s. - he went away, and the servant said he had taken something; I followed him, and found this telescope under his coat.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260622-87-person575">
                  SARAH 
                  WOODMAN
